##I get more information than others, and I suffer more pain than others

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

And then I thought about it, and it was scary, too. When I saw my aunt, I examined her, and she coughed on me.

Dictation | Song Yafeng

Arrangement | Huang Qi

"All of a sudden, I heard the news, I was in a bad mood, I was afraid, I didn't know him at all, but I felt very sad, have a good trip, I hope your family can pull through! " On February 7, i was particularly upset when a doctor in Wuhan died of a new coronavirus. I read the message in my friend circle. It was my 15th day in the new Corpulmonale.

I'm a gastrointestinal and anorectal surgeon, and the Fourth Wuhan Hospital, where I work, was one of the first new crown hospitals in Wuhan to be requisitioned. From New Year's Eve on duty into the new pneumonia isolation ward, the first round of work until the end of the Lantern Festival, I am now arranged by the government of the hotel isolation rotation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Song is in isolation

Think about what I've been through this past month? Let's just say I'm lucky I got a new one without any protection, and it's fine. Colleagues around the collapse of colleagues, colleagues are still living in my ward, think of the reality of what has happened, there is a deep sense of powerlessness.

I've been trying to clear my head lately, but my head's all over the place.

The patient who was later diagnosed coughed on me

It was an unprepared war that began a little earlier than reported.

By late December, I had heard about the first case of pneumonia of unknown origin reported by the Wuhan Health and Health Commission, and by late December, I had heard about the establishment of respiratory infectious disease quarantine zones in some hospitals. Wuhan has a small circle of doctors, most of whom are either Wuhan University graduates or Tongji Medical College graduates. In this circle, the news of doctors talking about unidentified pneumonia through wechat groups has spread.

By December 31, the Wuhan Health Commission had reported 27 cases of viral pneumonia.

I was a gastrointestinal and anorectal surgeon, and I didn't usually come into contact with respiratory disease patients, and at the time, the official line was, "this infection is only transmitted from person to person, " so even though I knew there was an infection, but there wasn't much protection at work. No one did.

On January 17th, an old patient of mine came to see me. She is a 60-year-old aunt, a few years ago had intestinal cancer surgery, postoperative recovery is good, did not do radiation and chemotherapy, has been in my regular review here. Each review, there are no signs of recurrence, there is no other basic disease, the overall state of good.

She came in with diarrhea, nausea, diarrhea for four days, no respiratory symptoms, occasional cough. She said she had a meal with a friend four days ago and came home with diarrhea. I did a CT of her abdomen, and there's nothing wrong with her bowel, and I can't find a cause for her diarrhea.

Two days after admission to the hospital, Ayi presented fever, dry cough, hoarseness. I ordered a chest CT right away, took a look at it, and I highly doubt it's what she has. That's what they called it back then -- a "viral lung" .

Call Radiology and double-check.

My aunt was very conscious and trusted me, and I gave her some treatment, from Nasal Cannula to oxygen mask to oxygen, the condition is still getting worse.

Highly suspicious, I called respiratory for an emergency consult. The suction doctor came in, took some meds, but it's still getting worse. It was impossible to transfer the patient to the respiratory department, which was already full, and some pneumonia patients were admitted to other medical departments.

By the 21st, my aunt was already very sick, I managed to transfer her to the respiratory department, on the high-flow oxygen therapy, and then to the non-invasive suction machine, and ultimately failed to save her.

This virus is particularly strange, the patient is always awake, the seriously ill patients is not up to oxygen, hypoxia. Looking at the patient's strong desire for life, the desire for life, while we doctors can only watch a life pass away but can not do anything about it, that kind of oppression, that kind of heavy, that kind of helplessness, that kind of self-reproach, that kind of helplessness, it's enough to crush us.

On January 23, our hospital announced that it had been requisitioned as a designated hospital for new pneumonia patients. All the doctors were on duty to manage the new crown isolation ward. At this time asked our doctor to do an examination, my lung CT showed that is good, it should be all right.

I don't know, Lucky. My friends say I was lucky in a past life.

A co-worker got infected and moved into my ward

Since January, the hospital has been full of smokers. In order to admit these pneumonia patients, the hospital began to expand the ward, other sections of the ward to make room for pneumonia patients. Clear out a section, fill it up quickly, and open a new one.

We as doctors know that the situation is not optimistic, at the end of December a hospital doctor was sent to reinforce the hospital, one of my classmates in another general hospital, was also sent to reinforce the hospital. That's when we knew it was serious.

My hospital is a general hospital, usually less use of isolation protective clothing such as high-level protective materials, people are not strong awareness of this, we only surgical disposable masks. So far, we don't have enough protection. The doctors saw N951860 as a kind of green mask, and both eyes lit up.

Our hospital has more than 2,000 employees. As of January 14, there were 53 confirmed and suspected cases of NCP among the medical staff. People out there might think that respiratory paramedics are more likely to get infected, but they're not. At the beginning, we lack of awareness of this disease, poor awareness of protection, other departments in the fall more.

Now the atmosphere between colleagues is also very strange, perhaps you see this colleague is still well today, perhaps tomorrow will have an attack, diagnosed. So the necessary distance between colleagues is also responsible for their own.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Song Yafeng

I was officially on duty on New Year's Eve in the new corpulmonale. My class of 5 doctors, is from different departments combination of the treatment program is mainly in accordance with the treatment guidelines, in fact, there is no specific medicine, mainly symptomatic treatment. My own experience so far, Immunoglobulin, oxygen therapy has a good effect, as long as the patient can survive 7-10 days, most can be carried over.

About 10 percent of the patients in my ward are very sick, and we have 38 patients at our peak. Especially heavy patients can not transfer out, because the ambulance does not have this high-pressure oxygen equipment in the ward, so the road is too dangerous.

I have some colleagues in this ward. One in particular stuck with me. He's an M.D. in his 30s. He was so negative at first, he didn't think he was gonNA make it out of here alive, and then we transferred him to smoking, and then to golden pond. The referral was risky, and I was grateful to my colleagues in the suction department, who had packed up their tracheotomy bags and escorted them by ambulance to the Golden Pool Hospital, where, thankfully, he was transferred from the ICU to the general ward.

Just hang in there till morning

On the day of Lantern Festival, I came out of the hospital room and took a rest.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A heavy snow falls in Wuhan on February 15

There is also good news. Our first batch of first echelon epidemic prevention medical and nursing staff achieved zero infection of medical and nursing staff and zero death of patients in their quarantined wards. More than 20 people recovered smoothly and were discharged from hospital, achieving the goal of victory in stages.

The stress of being on the front line was great, and during my isolation break I tried to adjust my mindset and sleep improved dramatically. At first I suspected that I had a traumatic psychological disorder, I have a senior daily counseling me, told me to watch less online news, read every day to listen to music. He said one of his colleagues in the Infectious Diseases Department had a near-collapse, which was later alleviated by this method.

Well, I get more information than anyone else, so I suffer more than anyone else.

A while ago a broadcast media interview, I cry in the radio, it is really very embarrassed, the director cut to another hospital nurses, nurses also cry in the radio.

With Wuhan taking strong control measures, the blockade of Wuhan has largely prevented the virus from spreading nationally and globally. But for Wuhan, after three of the most difficult weeks, it was overwhelmed.

With the expansion of hospital beds, the construction of shelters, the putting into use of Mount Vulcan and Mount Thor, with the constant flow of material assistance throughout the country, with the support of medical care throughout the country, we have gone from the initial panic and disorder, slowly getting back on track.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Song's wife is also a doctor

It's GonNa be light. We're hanging in there.
